	<h2 id="key-takeaways" class="vf-u-margin--0 vf-u-padding__top--400 vf-u-padding__bottom--600">Key takeaways</h2>
	<p>
		Anti-patterns highlight design approaches that significantly reduce system performance and accessibility in
		low-resource environments.
	</p>
	<p>
		By recognising practices such as SPA-only architectures, heavy 3D rendering, infinite scrolling, and unbounded
		API calls, developers can avoid inefficient implementations and adopt more resource-efficient alternatives.
	</p>
	<p>
		Avoiding these anti-patterns ensures that digital systems remain accessible, performant, and scalable across
		diverse network conditions.
	</p>

